DISEASE PREDICTION SYSTEM

ABSTRACT

The Disease Prediction System is a machine learning-based application that predicts possible diseases based on the symptoms entered by the user. The system helps users obtain an early indication of diseases and encourages timely medical consultation. It uses historical disease datasets and machine learning algorithms to analyze symptoms and provide predictions with improved accuracy.

INTRODUCTION

Healthcare is one of the most important sectors where technology can play a significant role. Many diseases can be identified at an early stage by analyzing symptoms. The Disease Prediction System is designed to assist users in predicting diseases quickly and efficiently using machine learning techniques. The system reduces manual effort and provides preliminary information regarding health conditions.

OBJECTIVES

- To predict diseases based on user symptoms.
- To provide fast and accurate results.
- To reduce the time required for preliminary diagnosis.
- To apply machine learning techniques in healthcare.
- To help users seek medical attention at an early stage.

PROBLEM STATEMENT

Traditional disease diagnosis requires medical consultation and laboratory tests, which may consume time and resources. There is a need for a system that can provide an initial prediction of diseases based on symptoms entered by users. The Disease Prediction System addresses this issue by using machine learning models to generate predictions efficiently.

METHODOLOGY

1. Collect disease and symptom datasets.
2. Preprocess the data by removing missing values and encoding categorical data.
3. Train a machine learning model using the dataset.
4. Accept symptoms from the user.
5. Predict the disease using the trained model.
6. Display the predicted disease as output.

